(originally posted by @yannireddit on 2023-10-10 19:15:44)</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/DBgmlK6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ThisTimeLastYear]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Coaches Tot casserole!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/D6T0nln</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/j8t1tah.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/D6T0nln</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Zaboom16]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Keep ‘em scared…</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/wrnkDgK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UnQ08S2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/wrnkDgK</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Fanner50]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I quit my job at Bethesda after 14 years and made this heavy metal horror game as a solo dev with no publisher. Now it comes out in less than two weeks!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Q6KEpVJ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wBYylKq.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>So I went ahead and did it, I did the whole "I'm going to quit my job and make an indie game" thing haha. I had always wanted to do it, and Unreal 5 looked really cool and I had a lot of experience making open worlds, so I quit on April 1st 2021. :D (Some people obviously didn't believe me at the time due to the date haha)</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/iEMOaaT.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I hope you all think the game looks cool!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/I8sWkeP.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It took about 3.5 years, but now it's actually coming out in less than two weeks. I'm really excited to see what people think of it and it has been cool watching streamers react to the demo. Somehow my two story tall tree guy is really good at sneaking up on people. :D</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/DqdgeKA.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I did this whole thing without a publisher, which is a huge gamble. The only positive income I've had for 3.5 years is the MegaGrant I got, which does not exactly fund the whole thing. (Not even close, but it was very cool of Epic) So I'll find out in a couple weeks if that was a great idea or a terrible one. It has been nice having no one over me telling me what to do or when to do it by. Also then they don't take 50% of my profits... forever. Which seems... not great.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fieuF9D.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I did get some help along the way, I somehow got Clifford Meyer from the band Isis (!!! one of my favorites) to do the whole soundtrack, someone did the journal drawings, I had a few writers and my wife helped me sort out the lore and handle the boring business stuff I'm awful at, but other than that I had to do the rest. So world art, animation, character art, fx, sound, marketing, bizdev, systems design, level design, etc. etc. etc.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Nyb5k2g.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>So if you have any questions about what it's like being a solo dev, working with Unreal, questions about Skyrim/Fallout and working on those, let me know!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Q6KEpVJ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[JustPurkeyGames]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>This secret sliding door to hide a safe</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/EhMWrav</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fwnzDCz.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></d